The paper discusses the use of Agent-Oriented Software Engineering (AOSE) methodologies in modeling the Multiple Sclerosis brain disease. This involves the use of multiagent-based simulation models and brain complex networks, which are all related to artificial intelligence and multiagent systems. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.MA are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of software engineering principles in various phases of the model development, which relates to cs.SE. The paper also involves the development of a model replicating previous results, which involves the use of exploratory agent-based modeling, which relates to cs.SY. Finally, the paper discusses the modeling of a complex living system, which relates to cs.NE.
